 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search HR Coordinator Novant Health 1,747 reviews Winston-Salem, NC 27103 Full-time Novant Health 1,747 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Overview:
 
The HR Coordinator provides project coordination and orchestration of strategic people and culture initiatives to support the HR Executive Team and the organization. This position will execute and monitor strategic initiatives, enable and support exceptional change management, and communicate effectively to drive HR transformation, operational enhancements, and strategic improvements. Reporting to the HR Executive Team, this position requires a blend of strong consultative and critical thinking skills with keen knowledge of project management best practices. This position may specialize in talent acquisition, total rewards, strategic initiatives, solutions center operations, new hire onboarding, leadership development, student programs, or engagement and retention. Ability to think critically in a fast-paced environment and demonstrates visible momentum 
Qualifications:
 
Education: Bachelor's degree required. 
Experience: A minimum of one year of the following experience is required- project management with an emphasis on budget management, board preparation, merger and acquisition, related healthcare industry, communications, and/or human resources, artificial intelligence, and IT experience. Experience may include cocoordinating large scale, enterprise wide projects. 
Additional skills required: 
Advanced experience with MSOffice, particularly MS Excel, PowerPoint, Word 
Proficient with one or more of the following tools, iCIMS, PeopleSoft, ServiceNow, Infor, PowerBi, Tableau 
Experience preparing and analyzing budget data with attention to accurate data and calculations 
Ability to effectively communicate and build relationships with a view of inclusion and belonging 
Analytical, consulting, organizational, and strategic thinking skills are required 
Action oriented, willing to do what is needed in order to move projects forward in an organized manner with consistent execution 
Strong digital fluency 
Relationship management skills that include listening and consultative abilities, as well as the ability to establish credible relationships with business partners to drive change 
Experience managing highly sensitive and confidential information 
Additional skills preferred: 
Entrepreneurial spirit and innovative drive for reaching the next great idea and exceeding goals 
Intellectual depth, moral integrity, personal vision, creativity, leadership skills, fortitude, sincerity and diplomacy 
Ability to work independently and as a team player who will productively engage with others at varying levels of seniority within and outside of Novant Health 
Bilingual in Spanish / English 
Responsibilities:
 
It is the responsibility of every Novant Health team member to deliver the most remarkable patient experience in every dimension, every time. 
Our team members are part of an environment that fosters team work, team member engagement and community involvement. 
The successful team member has a commitment to leveraging diversity and inclusion in support of quality care. 
All Novant Health team members are responsible for fostering a safe patient environment driven by the principles of "First Do No Harm". Novant Health 8 days ago original job Report job You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Human Resources Coordinator jobs in Winston-Salem, NC Jobs at Novant Health in Winston-Salem, NC Human Resources Coordinator salaries in Winston-Salem, NC Company Info Follow Get job updates from Novant Health Novant Health 1,747 reviews At Novant Health, you’ll find exceptional facilities, advanced medical treatments, and an amazing team in North Carolina, Virginia and So... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume 
 
